adopted, partly by translation for <i>Ó Cléirigh</i>; see   Cleary  .","Americanized form of Dutch   De Klerk   or Flemish   De Clerck   or of variants of these names, and possibly also of French   Clerc  . Compare   Clerk   2 and   De Clark  ."]}]},{"name":"Alis","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Alice","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."]},{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alis Clarke married Robert Panstone on 4 May 1541, in London, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1527–1600":"1527–1600","–Female":"Surnud","1600":"1600","4 May 1541":"4. mai 1541","1527":"1527","St. Mildred Poultry's Church, London, England":"London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, Devonshire, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1527–1600":"1527–1600","–Female":"Kuollut","1600":"1600","4 May 1541":"4. toukokuuta 1541","1527":"1527","St. Mildred Poultry's Church, London, England":"London, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devon, Devonshire, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1527–1600":"1527–1600","–Female":"Décédée","1600":"1600","4 May 1541":"4 mai 1541","1527":"1527","St. Mildred Poultry's Church, London, England":"Londres, Anglet